From 0fb118de5003028ad092a4e66fc6d07b86c3bc94 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Herve Codina <herve.codina@bootlin.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Oct 2023 17:30:12 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: muxes: i2c-demux-pinctrl: Use of_get_i2c_adapter_by_node()
Git-commit: 0fb118de5003028ad092a4e66fc6d07b86c3bc94
Patch-mainline: v6.6
References: git-fixes

i2c-demux-pinctrl uses the pair of_find_i2c_adapter_by_node() /
i2c_put_adapter(). These pair alone is not correct to properly lock the
I2C parent adapter.

Indeed, i2c_put_adapter() decrements the module refcount while
of_find_i2c_adapter_by_node() does not increment it. This leads to an
underflow of the parent module refcount.

Use the	dedicated function, of_get_i2c_adapter_by_node(), to handle
correctly the module refcount.

Fixes: 50a5ba876908 ("i2c: mux: demux-pinctrl: add driver")
Signed-off-by: Herve Codina <herve.codina@bootlin.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Acked-by: Peter Rosin <peda@axentia.se>
Reviewed-by: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Wolfram Sang <wsa@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-demux-pinctrl.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-demux-pinctrl.c b/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-demux-pinctrl.c
index 22f2280eab7f..9f2e4aa28159 100644
--- a/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-demux-pinctrl.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-demux-pinctrl.c
@@ -61,7 +61,7 @@ static int i2c_demux_activate_master(struct i2c_demux_pinctrl_priv *priv, u32 ne
 	if (ret)
 		goto err;
 
-	adap = of_find_i2c_adapter_by_node(priv->chan[new_chan].parent_np);
+	adap = of_get_i2c_adapter_by_node(priv->chan[new_chan].parent_np);
 	if (!adap) {
 		ret = -ENODEV;
 		goto err_with_revert;
